HEADWORD: Purulent
<hw>Pu"ru*lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>purulentus</ets>, fr. <ets>pus</ets>, <ets>puris</ets>, pus,
matter: cf. F. <ets>purulent</ets>. See <er>Pus</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Consisting of pus, or matter; partaking of the
nature of pus; attended with suppuration; <as>as, <ex>purulent</ex>
inflammation</as>.</def><-- sic. What kind of "matter"? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Purulently</ent>⟦br⟧
